race.comment: MARVEL MAN (1) continued his excellent run of form when narrowly beaten over 1100m at Bathurst last start. Kept fresh since that run a month ago which usually works well. Will race handy and prove tough to hold out in a deep field. REAL DELUXE (2) took on open company when fresh from a spell last time and did a good job to be beaten only 3.5 lengths over 900m at Muswellbrook. Good second-up performer who is at her best over 1000m. Big danger back in this company. KEADOOL (6) ran his usual honest race last start, boxing on well for a close third over 1100m at Coonamble. Kept fresh since that outing five weeks ago. Should be about the mark again. PELETTE (8) is a chance if she finds the form that saw her beaten a whisker over this distance at Muswellbrook two back. CHICKEN LEGS (5) gets in well after the claim and will enjoy dropping back in trip.
